This method takes a matrix and the row and column of the element for which the cofactor is required, and returns the cofactor matrix. The cofactor of an element in a matrix is calculated by taking the determinant of the submatrix formed by deleting the row and column of the element and multiplying it by -1^(i+j), where i and j are the row and column indices of the element, respectively.

