public <T> T mergeWith(String key, T x, BiFunction<? super T, ? super T, ? extends T> accumulatorFunction) {
    Objects.requireNonNull(key);
    Objects.requireNonNull(accumulatorFunction);

    // Get the previous value associated with the key
    T oldValue = getOrDefault(key, null);

    // Combine the previous value with the new value using the accumulator function
    T newValue = (oldValue == null) ? x : accumulatorFunction.apply(oldValue, x);

    // Store the new value associated with the key and return the old value
    put(key, newValue);
    return oldValue;
}
```

This method takes in a key and a value to be merged with the existing value associated with the key (if any). The merge operation is performed by the provided accumulator function, which takes in the old value (or zero, if there is none) and the new value, and returns the merged value.

