This method takes an integer value `x`, a byte buffer `buf`, and an offset `offset` as input parameters. It writes the integer value to the byte buffer in little-endian format starting at the specified offset.

To write an integer value in little-endian format, we need to break down the integer into 4 bytes and write them in reverse order to the byte buffer. In the above code, we first write the least significant byte of the integer value to the byte buffer, followed by the second least significant byte, and so on, until we write the most significant byte of the integer value. This way, the integer value is written to the byte buffer in little-endian format.

