public double computeDecompositionQuality(Matrix A, Matrix L, Matrix U) {
    Matrix P = L.times(U).minus(A);
    double errorNorm = P.normInf();
    double tolerance = Math.max(Math.max(A.norm1(), L.norm1() * U.norm1()), Double.MIN_VALUE) * Double.EPSILON;
    return errorNorm / tolerance;
}
```

Note: The code assumes that the input matrices A, L, and U are already initialized and populated with appropriate values. The normInf() method returns the maximum absolute value of any element in the matrix. The norm1() method returns the maximum column sum of the matrix. Double.EPSILON is the smallest value that can be added to 1.0 to get a result different from 1.0 in double precision.

